    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Power Cylinder - Removal - Piston Disassembly</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26507.1.3" svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Piston Disassembly</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, wear safety glasses when removing retaining
                    rings. See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="safety">"Safety Information</hotlnk>."
                </para>
            </warning>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, mark the pistons with the cylinder number from which each was removed.
                    Each piston must be reinstalled into its original cylinder bore, if the pistons are being reused.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e300808" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd04/D0401.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the piston rings</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston ring expansion pliers</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston ring</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use Piston Ring Expansion Pliers to remove the piston rings. Remove top ring first,
                intermediate ring, and then finally the oil control ring. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_167.xml" xrefid="E3008C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e300809" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd04/D0402.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the piston pin retaining ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Separate connecting rod from piston as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Use pliers to remove both piston pin retaining rings.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove piston pin from its bore by hand, and then separate connecting rod from piston.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
